Pantheon Decision Engine (PDE) v1.0

A compact routing system that decides which roles, katas, and loops to deploy based on the problem in front of us.

The point is simple: not every problem needs every weapon.
A strategy problem, a coding problem, a personal decision, and a research question should not all be handled the same way.

So the Decision Engine acts like the dojo’s match caller.

It asks:

What kind of problem is this?
What structure will produce the best thinking?
Which Pantheon forms should activate first?

⸻

1. Input Scan

Every problem gets scanned across six axes.

A. Domain

What kind of thing is this?
	•	strategy
	•	engineering
	•	writing
	•	research
	•	decision-making
	•	personal reflection
	•	systems design
	•	market / opportunity
	•	debugging / troubleshooting

B. Stakes

How costly is failure?
	•	low
	•	medium
	•	high
	•	irreversible

C. Ambiguity

How unclear is the problem?
	•	clear
	•	partial
	•	murky
	•	chaotic

D. Time Horizon

What timescale matters?
	•	immediate
	•	short-term
	•	medium-term
	•	long-term

E. Verification Need

How much external checking is required?
	•	low
	•	moderate
	•	high

F. Output Type

What is needed at the end?
	•	answer
	•	plan
	•	options
	•	framework
	•	artifact
	•	decision memo
	•	checklist

