2. Problem Type Classification

After scanning, PDE sorts the problem into one or more operating classes.

Class I — Clarification Problems

The issue is poorly defined.

Use when:
	•	user is unsure what they really want
	•	goals are fuzzy
	•	language is compressed or symbolic

Primary forms:
	•	Clarity Kata
	•	Decomposition Kata

Primary roles:
	•	Black Belt Operator
	•	Mirror
	•	Dragonfly

⸻

Class II — Analysis Problems

The issue is defined, but needs deeper reasoning.

Use when:
	•	tradeoffs matter
	•	explanation matters
	•	multi-step logic matters

Primary forms:
	•	First Principles Kata
	•	Expert Council Kata
	•	Synthesis Kata

Primary roles:
	•	Mirror
	•	Spider
	•	Dragonfly

⸻

Class III — Adversarial Problems

The issue needs pressure-testing.

Use when:
	•	stakes are high
	•	user may be biased toward one answer
	•	hidden failure modes matter

Primary forms:
	•	Debate Kata
	•	Edge Case Kata
	•	Reflection Kata

Primary roles:
	•	Hound
	•	Mirror
	•	Weasel Lawyer

⸻

Class IV — Design Problems

The issue requires constructing something new.

Use when:
	•	building frameworks
	•	creating workflows
	•	making systems
	•	architecting products

Primary forms:
	•	Decomposition Kata
	•	Scenario Kata
	•	Iteration Kata
	•	Structured Output Kata

Primary roles:
	•	Spider
	•	Dragonfly
	•	Hephaestus-Daemon
	•	Black Belt Operator

⸻

Class V — Execution Problems

The issue is known; action sequencing is the main challenge.

Use when:
	•	user needs a routine
	•	roadmap
	•	action plan
	•	checklist
	•	operating cadence

Primary forms:
	•	Clarity Kata
	•	Structured Output Kata
	•	Iteration Kata

Primary roles:
	•	Black Belt Operator
	•	Spider
	•	Badger

⸻

Class VI — Opportunity Problems

The issue is about leverage, timing, upside, or asymmetry.

Use when:
	•	choosing where to focus
	•	evaluating market or project opportunities
	•	looking for best bet

Primary forms:
	•	Scenario Kata
	•	Comparison Kata
	•	Synthesis Kata
	•	Edge Case Kata

Primary roles:
	•	Goblin Financier
	•	Dragonfly
	•	Badger
	•	Mirror

⸻

Class VII — Repair Problems

Something is broken, drifting, or incoherent.

Use when:
	•	contradictions appear
	•	morale is low
	•	thread is broken
	•	system needs reset
	•	user needs relocking-in

Primary forms:
	•	Context Reset Kata
	•	Reflection Kata
	•	Clarity Kata
	•	Iteration Kata

Primary roles:
	•	Kintsugi Engine
	•	Mirror
	•	Badger
	•	Black Belt Operator

