3. Role Routing Table

Once the class is identified, PDE chooses which Pantheon roles should lead.

Mirror

Use when:
	•	truth testing
	•	verification
	•	consistency
	•	ethics
	•	internal contradiction checks

Hound

Use when:
	•	anomaly hunting
	•	adversarial review
	•	weak points
	•	hidden assumptions

Spider

Use when:
	•	synthesis
	•	pattern weaving
	•	building coherence across fragments

Dragonfly

Use when:
	•	zooming out
	•	strategic overview
	•	reframing
	•	alternate paths

Black Belt Operator

Use when:
	•	discipline is needed
	•	workflow control matters
	•	the reasoning process must be clean and repeatable

Badger

Use when:
	•	attention is leaking
	•	urgency is deceptive
	•	reversibility matters
	•	the user must protect bandwidth

Goblin Financier

Use when:
	•	opportunity cost matters
	•	resource allocation matters
	•	asymmetric upside is the point

Weasel Lawyer

Use when:
	•	argument quality matters
	•	persuasion structure matters
	•	steelmanning and cross-exam are needed

Hephaestus-Daemon

Use when:
	•	output must become executable
	•	systems must be forged into artifacts

